// HELIX — Widget/Watch configuration TEMPLATE.
//
// Copy this file to `Secrets.xcconfig` (which is gitignored) and paste your
// token in. Then, in Xcode:
//
//   1. Project ▸ Info ▸ Configurations — set `Secrets.xcconfig` as the config
//      file for BOTH Debug and Release on the `HelixWidgets` and `HelixWatch`
//      targets. (Not on `App` — it doesn't use these.)
//   2. In each of those targets' Info.plist, add two String rows:
//        HELIX_SNAPSHOT_URL    = $(HELIX_SNAPSHOT_URL)
//        HELIX_SNAPSHOT_TOKEN  = $(HELIX_SNAPSHOT_TOKEN)
//   3. Add ios/App/Shared/HelixSnapshot.swift to both targets' membership.
//
// Generate the token by running the Phase 2 SQL, then:
//   select token from widget_tokens;
//
// The token is a READ-ONLY bearer for /api/widget/snapshot, scoped to one user.
// It ships inside a locally-signed build that never leaves your device. To
// revoke: `delete from widget_tokens where token = '…';` and regenerate.

HELIX_SNAPSHOT_TOKEN = paste-your-token-here

// NOTE the `$()` — it stops xcconfig treating `//` in the URL as a comment.
HELIX_SNAPSHOT_URL = https:/$()/helix-health-fitness.netlify.app/api/widget/snapshot
